 :tx/rationale "PERF-ROOT-CAUSE: braid status takes 8.5s (release binary, 33k datoms). Store load is only 0.7s (cache works). The 7.8s is COMPUTATION. Root cause is two-fold: (1) REDUNDANT COMPUTATION: build_json and build_status_projection both independently call compute_fitness, methodology_gaps, default_boundaries().evaluate_all, derive_actions — every expensive function runs TWICE. (2) INDEX BYPASS: bilateral.rs has 7 calls to store.datoms() (full O(n) scan over 33,800 datoms) and 0 calls to attribute_datoms() (O(k) index lookup). trilateral.rs has 3 full scans and 0 index lookups. Meanwhile guidance.rs uses 17 index lookups and only 4 full scans — which is why R(t) routing is fast (0.35s) while bilateral is slow (1.4s). The AEVT index exists, is maintained at write time, is tested (proptest), but is NEVER USED by the two modules that need it most. Key measurements: :impl/implements has 1,146 datoms (vs 33,800 total = 3.4%), :spec/element-type has 502 (1.5%), :task/status has 1,635 (4.8%), :exploration/category has 363 (1.1%). Index lookups would be 20-90x faster than full scans. TRACES TO: INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-STORE-005, INV-QUERY-025."
